      • getMU

        public UniformDistribution getMU(com.google.common.geometry.S2CellId cell)
        This will return the mu uniform distribution for the requested S2CellId. The S2CellId HashMap is quite small so is cached here for speed, rather than querying the DAO each time.
        Parameters:
        cell - The S2CellId for which the MU is required
        Returns:
        UniformDistribution of the MU. May be null if no information exists for the specified cell.

      • getS2Polygon

        public static com.google.common.geometry.S2Polygon getS2Polygon(long lat1,
                                                                long lng1,
                                                                long lat2,
                                                                long lng2,
                                                                long lat3,
                                                                long lng3)
        Assembles a Triangular S2Polygon for the specified points. The points are in integer E6 format (divide by 1E6 (1,000,000) to get floating point coordinates)
        Parameters:
        lat1 - The Latitude of point 1 in E6 format
        lng1 - The Longitude of point 1 in E6 format
        lat2 - The Latitude of point 2 in E6 format
        lng2 - The Longitude of point 2 in E6 format
        lat3 - The Latitude of point 3 in E6 format
        lng3 - The Longitude of point 3 in E6 format
        Returns:
        S2Polygon of the triangle

      • getS2Polygon

        public static com.google.common.geometry.S2Polygon getS2Polygon(com.google.common.geometry.S2Point v1,
                                                                com.google.common.geometry.S2Point v2,
                                                                com.google.common.geometry.S2Point v3)
        Assembles a triangular S2Polygon from S2Point points This method uses the S2PolygonBuilder of an Undirected Union so that the points may be in any winding order (CW or CCW) and the resulting polygon is always smaller than the region is doesn't cover.
        Parameters:
        v1 - S2Point of point 1
        v2 - S2Point of point 2
        v3 - S2Point of point 3
        Returns:
        S2Polygon of the Triangle

      • getIntersectionMU

        public java.util.HashMap<com.google.common.geometry.S2CellId,AreaDistribution> getIntersectionMU(com.google.common.geometry.S2Polygon thisField)
        Generates an intersection map of a Field and its cells. Returns a HashMap of the S2CellId and its area in Km^2 and the min and max MU for that cell.

      • muFieldValid

        public boolean muFieldValid(com.google.common.geometry.S2Polygon s2Field,
                            int mu)
        Determines if a field's mu is possibly valid. Requires adequate cell data for the field being tested if not enough cell data is available this method will return true.
        Parameters:
        s2Field - The field to test.
        mu - the integer value of the field. Fields have floating point mu values but are rounded to the nearest integer greater than 0
        Returns:
        boolean indicating if the MU specified agrees with the cell data.

        public void processField(Field field)
